flowRoot.flowPara: Shared edges don't have "corners" - it isn't possible to change direction when dragging a thumbnail that is attached to another. In the following example, it wouldn't be possible to move the thumbnail to the left, other than to detach it from the joined edge it shares with the other display.

flowRoot.flowPara: Free-drag mode will also end when a thumbnail is dragged between other thumbnails. Ideally there would be some hint about this, such as the other displays making space as the thumbnail is dragged close to the gap.

flowRoot.flowPara: Drag and drop ends when an edge of the dragged thumbnail comes into contact with the edge of another thumbnail. At this point, the thumbnail becomes fully opaque and an adjustment area is instated.

flowRoot.flowPara: Thumbnails that have joined edges along multiple axes can only be dragged to detach - they cannot be adjusted along a single axis.
General rules that are enforced by the display arrangement widget at all times:
- Every display must always share part of an edge with another display.
- Each shared edge should have a minimum length.

flowRoot.flowPara: Gaps between displays are not permitted when realigning. To acheive this, when one display is dragged, other attached displays will move with it. In the case below, displays 1 and 2 would move as a unit when dragged horizontally, while 2 and 3 would move as a unit if the pointer moved vertically.
Alignment adjustment
Sliding realignment occurs when a display is dragged and the pointer stays within available adjustment areas (these are indicated by the red dashed lines below).
Each alignment area runs parallel to a joined edge that the dragged display can be realigned against.
Drag and drop
In this design there are two types of drag mode:
1. Alignment adjustment
2. Drag and drop

flowRoot.flowPara: 3. Pointer moves outside the adjustment area and the display is detached
When a display has detached:
- It is taken out of the displayed arrangement and the other displays rearrange as if it isn't present
- The dragged thumbnail is semi-transparent and can overlay the other displays
- Releasing the drag while the thumbnail is in an invalid position restores the previous arrangement
- Pressing Esc cancels the drag
